        "content": "<p>I'm working on a natural numbers game level (World 9, Level 4), solved it, and am now exploring other proofs to that level.  I know Lean has <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib_docs/data/nat/basic.html#nat.le_induction\"><code>le_induction</code></a> that starts from a different  base case (e.g. n=1) but in NNG we have <code>induction</code>. Is there a way to change the basis of <code>induction</code>?</p>\n<p>I attempted to do this with,</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"k\">have</span> <span class=\"n\">a</span> <span class=\"o\">:=</span> <span class=\"mi\">1</span> <span class=\"bp\">&lt;=</span> <span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"o\">,</span> <span class=\"c1\">-- \"error: failed to synthesize type class instance for for a b c : mynat,\"</span>\n<span class=\"n\">induction</span> <span class=\"n\">a</span> <span class=\"k\">with</span> <span class=\"n\">k</span> <span class=\"n\">h1</span><span class=\"o\">,</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>In Lean 4<br>\n<code>\ntheorem mul_left_cancel2 (a b c : nat) (ha : a ≠ 0) : a * b = a * c → b = c :=\nbegin\n  have a : 1 &lt;= a,\n</code><br>\ngives</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"mi\">2</span> <span class=\"n\">goals</span>\n<span class=\"n\">abc</span><span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">ℕ</span>\n<span class=\"n\">ha</span><span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">a</span> <span class=\"bp\">≠</span> <span class=\"mi\">0</span>\n<span class=\"bp\">⊢</span> <span class=\"mi\">1</span> <span class=\"bp\">≤</span> <span class=\"n\">a</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">abc</span><span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">ℕ</span>\n<span class=\"n\">ha</span><span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">a</span> <span class=\"bp\">≠</span> <span class=\"mi\">0</span>\n<span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"mi\">1</span> <span class=\"bp\">≤</span> <span class=\"n\">a</span>\n<span class=\"bp\">⊢</span> <span class=\"n\">a</span> <span class=\"bp\">*</span> <span class=\"n\">b</span> <span class=\"bp\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">a</span> <span class=\"bp\">*</span> <span class=\"n\">c</span> <span class=\"bp\">→</span> <span class=\"n\">b</span> <span class=\"bp\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">c</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>and I can continue to solve the level with a different proof.</p>",
